The paper deals with the problem of line spectrum denoising and estimation, which is a common topic in signal processing and information theory. The use of compressed sensing techniques and semidefinite programming suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SP (Signal Processing) sub-categories. The focus on sparse signals and dictionary learning also suggests a possible fit with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of numerical optimization and performance analysis suggests a possible fit with the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple measurement vectors and population covariance matrices suggests a possible fit with the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
